# Lists

## Unordered lists
To create a unordered list use
:::code
- item
- item
-1 item with 1 tab
-2 item with 2 tab
-2 item with 2 tab
-1 item with 1 tab
- item
:::

Result:

- item
- item
-1 item with 1 tab
-2 item with 2 tab
-2 item with 2 tab
-1 item with 1 tab
- item

## Ordered lists
To create a unordered with automatic numbers list use
:::code
+ item
+ item
+1 item with 1 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+1 item with 1 tab
+ item
:::

Result:

+ item
+ item
+1 item with 1 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+1 item with 1 tab
+ item


To create a unordered with manual numbers list use
:::code
1. item
2. item
3.1 item with 1 tab
4.2 item with 2 tab
5.2 item with 2 tab
6.1 item with 1 tab
7 item
:::

Result:

+    item
+ item
+1 item with 1 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+1 item with 1 tab
+ item

Or you can mix them
:::code
+ item
5. item //this will not work because the start from another number only works at the start of the list
9.1 item with 1 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+1 item with 1 tab
10. item
:::

Result:

+ item
5. item
9.1 item with 1 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+2 item with 2 tab
+1 item with 1 tab
10. item



:::note
In all types of list it can be as much spaces or tabs as you want to organise betwen te list element (+,-,1,1.2...) and the text
:::